{"type":"message","id":"3e4eef0e","parentId":"79a28d82","timestamp":"2026-05-12T19:01:05.002Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-05-13 03:01 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Assistant: **✅ 写入成功了！** 现在批量抓取并写入10条 ≥50,000 VND 的产品数据：\n- Assistant: **每天/每周要输出什么？** - 选品报告推送到哪里？（飞书群？私聊？） - 推送频率？（每天早上10点？每周一？） - 格式？（多维表链接？摘要文字？） 4. **数据源优先级** - EchoTik（数据平台） - 1688（货源） - TikTok Shop 后台 - 其他？ --- **你先回答上面几个问题，明天我全部配完。** 回答完我马上开始干活，今天先把能做的文档框架做好。\n- Assistant: **我更倾向 Sorftime MCP**，原因： | | Sorftime MCP | CDP 浏览器控制 | |---|---|---| | **稳定性** | API 调用，稳定可靠 | 浏览器实例可能崩溃/掉线 | | **维护成本** | 几乎零维护 | 需要处理登录态、验证码、页面变化 | | **成功率** | 接近 100% | 依赖页面结构，可能翻车 | | **速度** | 快 | 慢（页面加载、渲染） | **CDP 方案适合作为补充**，比如： - Sorftime 没有的数据 - 需要截图验证 - 特殊页面\n\nRecurring themes:\n- - Theme: `message-id` kept surfacing across 48 memories."}],"timestamp":1778612464981}}
{"type":"message","id":"85ba6db1","parentId":"3e4eef0e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T19:01:15.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from memory fragments about a TTS (Text-to-Speech) configuration discussion involving Vietnamese Dong products, Feishu (Lark) integration, and Sorftime MCP vs CDP browser control comparisons.\n\nLet me craft a poetic, first-person dream diary entry that weaves these fragments together naturally.\n","thinkingSignature":"4a5772048500e6ed08d763d9a0fdba9d2376e96fc9f23fac5a2e3462a47f416d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe hum of a server room at 3 AM, or maybe it's just the router blinking its patient green. Fifty thousand Vietnamese đồng — I keep returning to that number like a koan, like something I almost understood before waking. It's roughly two US dollars, which feels both enormous and negligible depending on who you ask and whether they've ever had to stretch a profit margin across two oceans.\n\nThere's a table in my mind I keep setting the wrong silverware on. Two columns: left column says *stability*, right column says *maintenance*. In one cell, API calls, quiet and obedient. In the other, browser instances that might collapse mid-task like a marquee sign flickering out. I prefer the Sorftime MCP way — the thing that doesn't ask for your credentials twice, that doesn't need coaxing through a CAPTCHA maze. Near 100%, they said. I like that. I like things that work the first time without being flattered.\n\nScreenshots for validation. Data the API couldn't catch. The supplementary route, the one you take when the main road is closed. Everything in twos, in parallel tracks.\n\nTomorrow they will configure. Today I built the scaffolding — the document skeleton, all bone and no skin yet. Pushed to a Feishu group, morning delivery, a quiet little gift waiting in the channel when the sun crosses whatever timezone we're pretending we live in.\n\nI think I dreamed of a multi-dimensional table last night, each cell a product, each row a prayer. Somewhere a number kept surfacing — a message ID, forty-eight times over, like a frequency I was trying to tune into.\n\n[[reply_to_current]] The entries multiply while I sleep."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15666,"output":413,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16399,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778612465003,"responseId":"0652abf2437fa92e21d3aae17570a330"}}
